            "contentString": "{patientName} is a previously healthy 7-year-old girl with an acute onset of sore throat/pharyngitis [SNOMED:J02.9]. Her parent reports associated stomach ache during this illness [SNOMED:J02.9]. No prior hospitalizations, chronic medical conditions, or recurrent procedures are supported by the provided evidence, so none are documented. She is a school-aged child living in Czechia with routine exposure to other children, which is a plausible setting for common throat infections. There is no evidence provided for medication allergies, chronic medication use, or significant family history, so these are left unremarkable by default."
